<paragraph id="8B4936A51613FFADFF2BFA7CFEFEFF8B" blockId="7.[151,902,1462,1523]" box="[151,301,1497,1523]" pageId="7" pageNumber="50">
(
<figureCitation id="13CD2A201613FFADFF23FA7CFEF6FF8B" box="[159,293,1497,1523]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 28–35" captionStart-1="FIGURES 36–38" captionStartId-0="9.[151,270,1732,1756]" captionStartId-1="10.[151,270,1450,1474]" captionTargetBox-0="[168,1419,204,1681]" captionTargetBox-1="[160,1421,515,1399]" captionTargetId-0="figure-124@9.[151,1436,194,1708]" captionTargetId-1="figure-292@10.[151,1436,506,1426]" captionTargetPageId-0="9" captionTargetPageId-1="10" captionText-0="FIGURES 28–35. Exogonia luteovittata sp. nov.: (28) body of female paratype, lateral view; (29) head, pronotum, and mesonotum of male paratype, dorsal view; (30–35) male holotype: (30) pygofer, lateral view; (31) subgenital plate, ventral view; (32) connective and style, dorsal view; (33) aedeagus and basal portion of gonoduct, lateral view; (34) paraphyses, lateral view; (35) paraphyses, dorsal view." captionText-1="FIGURES 36–38. Exogonia luteovittata sp. nov., female paratype: (36) sternite VII, ventral view; (37) pygofer, lateral view; (38) second valvula, lateral view." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321366" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321370" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/5321366/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/5321370/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="50">Figs 28–38</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B4936A51613FFADFF2BF983FB1BFC38" blockId="7.[151,1436,1574,2020]" box="[151,1224,1574,1600]" pageId="7" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis id="B982EAB71613FFADFF2BF983FF29FC38" bold="true" box="[151,250,1574,1600]" pageId="7" pageNumber="50">Length:</emphasis>
Male 
<typeStatus id="544D88071613FFADFEF9F983FE7CFC38" box="[325,431,1574,1600]" pageId="7" pageNumber="50">holotype</typeStatus>
, 5.6 mm; male 
<typeStatus id="544D88071613FFADFDDFF983FD18FC38" box="[611,715,1574,1600]" pageId="7" pageNumber="50">paratype</typeStatus>
, 6.3-6.7 mm; female 
<typeStatus id="544D88071613FFADFC79F983FBFEFC38" box="[965,1069,1574,1600]" pageId="7" pageNumber="50">paratype</typeStatus>
, 6.6-6.7 mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B4936A51613FFADFF79F9E8FEF2FD50" blockId="7.[151,1436,1574,2020]" pageId="7" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis id="B982EAB71613FFADFF79F9E8FE5BFC1F" bold="true" box="[197,392,1613,1639]" pageId="7" pageNumber="50">
Male 
<typeStatus id="544D88071613FFADFEACF9E8FE50FC1F" box="[272,387,1613,1639]" pageId="7" pageNumber="50">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
Head (
<figureCitation id="13CD2A201613FFADFE58F9E8FDA6FC1F" box="[484,629,1613,1639]" captionStart="FIGURES 28–35" captionStartId="9.[151,270,1732,1756]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,204,1681]" captionTargetId="figure-124@9.[151,1436,194,1708]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 28–35. Exogonia luteovittata sp. nov.: (28) body of female paratype, lateral view; (29) head, pronotum, and mesonotum of male paratype, dorsal view; (30–35) male holotype: (30) pygofer, lateral view; (31) subgenital plate, ventral view; (32) connective and style, dorsal view; (33) aedeagus and basal portion of gonoduct, lateral view; (34) paraphyses, lateral view; (35) paraphyses, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321366" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321366/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="50">Figs 28, 29</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, moderately produced, anterior margin narrowly rounded; median length of crown 2/3 interocular width and 2/5 transocular width; epicranial and frontogenal sutures distinct, temporal sutures partially visible; with pair of foveae externally to ocelli. Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="13CD2A201613FFADFA80F93FFF6BFCA3" captionStart="FIGURES 28–35" captionStartId="9.[151,270,1732,1756]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,204,1681]" captionTargetId="figure-124@9.[151,1436,194,1708]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 28–35. Exogonia luteovittata sp. nov.: (28) body of female paratype, lateral view; (29) head, pronotum, and mesonotum of male paratype, dorsal view; (30–35) male holotype: (30) pygofer, lateral view; (31) subgenital plate, ventral view; (32) connective and style, dorsal view; (33) aedeagus and basal portion of gonoduct, lateral view; (34) paraphyses, lateral view; (35) paraphyses, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321366" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321366/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="50">Figs 28, 29</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, with width slightly larger than transocular width. Forewings (
<figureCitation id="13CD2A201613FFADFBC9F964FB1DFCA3" box="[1141,1230,1729,1755]" captionStart="FIGURES 28–35" captionStartId="9.[151,270,1732,1756]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,204,1681]" captionTargetId="figure-124@9.[151,1436,194,1708]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 28–35. Exogonia luteovittata sp. nov.: (28) body of female paratype, lateral view; (29) head, pronotum, and mesonotum of male paratype, dorsal view; (30–35) male holotype: (30) pygofer, lateral view; (31) subgenital plate, ventral view; (32) connective and style, dorsal view; (33) aedeagus and basal portion of gonoduct, lateral view; (34) paraphyses, lateral view; (35) paraphyses, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321366" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321366/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="50">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
) with membrane slightly developed, extending from median portion of wing along costal margin and expanding apically on apical cells.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B4936A51613FFA2FF7AF890FCDBFAAF" blockId="7.[151,1436,1574,2020]" lastBlockId="8.[151,1436,152,215]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="51" pageId="7" pageNumber="50">
Ground color of dorsum (
<figureCitation id="13CD2A201613FFADFDB1F890FD73FD37" box="[525,672,1845,1871]" captionStart="FIGURES 28–35" captionStartId="9.[151,270,1732,1756]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,204,1681]" captionTargetId="figure-124@9.[151,1436,194,1708]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 28–35. Exogonia luteovittata sp. nov.: (28) body of female paratype, lateral view; (29) head, pronotum, and mesonotum of male paratype, dorsal view; (30–35) male holotype: (30) pygofer, lateral view; (31) subgenital plate, ventral view; (32) connective and style, dorsal view; (33) aedeagus and basal portion of gonoduct, lateral view; (34) paraphyses, lateral view; (35) paraphyses, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321366" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321366/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="50">Figs 28, 29</figureCitation>
) brown to dark brown; with two longitudinal yellow stripes extending from anterior margin of crown to apical portion of forewings; stripes convergent anteriorly on crown and pronotum. Forewings (
<figureCitation id="13CD2A201613FFADFD94F825FDADFDE2" box="[552,638,1920,1946]" captionStart="FIGURES 28–35" captionStartId="9.[151,270,1732,1756]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,204,1681]" captionTargetId="figure-124@9.[151,1436,194,1708]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 28–35. Exogonia luteovittata sp. nov.: (28) body of female paratype, lateral view; (29) head, pronotum, and mesonotum of male paratype, dorsal view; (30–35) male holotype: (30) pygofer, lateral view; (31) subgenital plate, ventral view; (32) connective and style, dorsal view; (33) aedeagus and basal portion of gonoduct, lateral view; (34) paraphyses, lateral view; (35) paraphyses, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321366" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321366/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="50">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
) with narrow yellow stripe along costal margin (other small yellow maculae are present). Face black; frons with few small yellow spots medially and near transition to crown; genae with anterior pale yellow macula; lora almost entirely pale yellow; posterolateral margin of head bordered with yellow; proepisternum almost entirely yellow; lateral pronotal lobes with lower and posterior portions yellow. Venter dark brown; legs pale yellow.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF89662D161CFFA2FF2BF8FCFDC2FDA4" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321364" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5321364" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321364/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="51" startId="8.[151,270,1881,1905]" targetBox="[173,1401,288,1857]" targetPageId="8">
